@node "System" "System requirements"
@next "Install"
@prev "Copyright"
@{b}System requirements@{ub}

To run BangerMenu you need Kickstart 2.04 or a later version. The gadtools.library
has to be in your "Libs:" directory. Since library is included in your
"Libs:" directory since Kickstart 2.04.
@endnode
@node "Install" "Installation"
@next "Parameter"
@prev "System"
@{b}Installation@{ub}

To install @{b}BangerMenu@{ub} onto a separate disc you should copy the program
@{b}BangerMenu@{ub} in your @{b}:c/@{ub} directory and the configuration file in
your @{b}:s/@{ub} directory.

To install @{b}BangerMenu@{ub} onto your hard disc you should copy the every file
of the program package into a directory, for example
@{fg highlight}"Work:Tools/BangerMenu"@{fg text}
or the same dirs like the discs


This is the top of the original startup-sequence.

@{b}; $VER: startup-sequence 39.9 (9.8.92)@{ub}

@{b}C:SetPatch QUIET
C:Version >NIL:
C:AddBuffers >NIL: DF0: 15
FailAt 21

C:MakeDir RAM:T RAM:Clipboards RAM:ENV RAM:ENV/Sys
C:Copy >NIL: ENVARC: RAM:ENV ALL NOREQ

Resident >NIL: C:Assign PURE
Resident >NIL: C:Execute PURE

Assign >NIL: ENV: RAM:ENV
Assign >NIL: T: RAM:T
Assign >NIL: CLIPS: RAM:Clipboards
Assign >NIL: REXX: S:@{ub}


@{i}  And this are the necessary changes, if you use BangerMenu without
  a particular monitor@{ui}

; $VER: startup-sequence @{fg highlight}40.3 (4-Sep-96)@{fg text}           ;the versionnr. not important
@{fg highlight}FailAt 21
C:
MakeDir RAM:T RAM:Clipboards RAM:ENV RAM:ENV/Sys@{fg text}   ;to create the T-dirctory to ram
@{fg highlight}Assign >NIL: ENV: RAM:ENV@{fg text}                          ;this is needed to run
@{fg highlight}Assign >NIL: T: RAM:T@{fg text}                              ;skripts by BangerMenu
@{fg highlight}Assign >NIL: CLIPS: RAM:Clipboards@{fg text}

@{b}<Pfad>@{ub}
@{b}BangerMenu@{ub}                                         ;this will be copied to
@{b}IF ERROR THEN@{ub}                                      ;startup-sequence
@{b} NewShell
 ENDCLI
ENDIF@{ub}

C:SetPatch QUIET
C:Version >NIL:
C:AddBuffers >NIL: DF0: 15

Resident >NIL: C:Assign PURE
Resident >NIL: C:Execute PURE

Assign >NIL: REXX: S:@{ub}


@{i}  And this are the necessary changes, if you use BangerMenu with a
   monitor like VGA or Euro72 (etc.)@{ui}

; $VER: startup-sequence @{fg highlight}40.3 (4-Sep-96)@{fg text}           ;the versionnr. not important
@{fg highlight}FailAt 21
C:
MakeDir RAM:T RAM:Clipboards RAM:ENV RAM:ENV/Sys@{fg text}   ;to create the T-dirctory to ram
@{fg highlight}Assign >NIL: ENV: RAM:ENV@{fg text}                          ;this is needed to run
@{fg highlight}Assign >NIL: T: RAM:T@{fg text}                              ;skripts by BangerMenu
@{fg highlight}Assign >NIL: CLIPS: RAM:Clipboards@{fg text}
@{fg highlight}C:SetPatch QUIET@{fg text}                                   ;this is necessary for the monitordriver

@{fg highlight}Copy >NIL: ENVARC: RAM:ENV ALL NOREQ@{fg text}

@{fg highlight}DEVS:Monitors/VGAOnly@{fg text}                              ;if VGAOnly in the Monitors-Dir, then you
                                                   ;must add this line to startup-sequence

@{b}<Pfad>@{ub}
@{b}BangerMenu MT=@{ub}<@{fg highlight}@{i}Treiber@{ui}@{fg text}> @{b}MONITORID@{ub}=<@{fg highlight}@{i}IDNumber@{ui}@{fg text}>          ;look at @{"usage" link "usage" 0}
@{b}IF ERROR THEN@{ub}
@{b} NewShell
 ENDCLI
ENDIF@{ub}

C:Version >NIL:
C:AddBuffers >NIL: DF0: 15

Resident >NIL: C:Assign PURE
Resident >NIL: C:Execute PURE

Assign >NIL: REXX: S:@{ub}

@endnode
@node "Parameter" "Commandoline"
@next "usage"
@prev "Install"
@{b}Commandoline@{ub}

@{fg highlight}FN=PREFSFILENAME/K,MT=MONITORTREIBER/K,MONITORID/K/N,NOKEY/S@{fg text}


 @{b}FN=PREFSFILENAME/K@{ub}: the name of the config
                     if you give no filename then @{b}BangerMenu@{ub} search for @{b}BangerMenu.prefs@{ub}
                     in the active dir and the S: dir.

@{b}MT=MONITORTREIBER/K@{ub}: give a name of the monitordriver for use a different solution.
                     Only with @{b}MONITORID@{ub}.

      @{b}MONITORID/K/N@{ub}: A number of a screensolution in decimal. You can find the right
                     number with the program @{"BangerMonitorID" link "BangerMonitorID" 0}.

            @{b}NOKEY/S@{ub}: @{b}BangerMenu@{ub} will appear every startup
@endnode
@node "usage" "How to use BangerMenu"
@next "Tastatur"
@prev "Parameter"
@{b}How to use BangerMenu@{ub}

BangerMenu can only be started by using the shell.

If you would like to see the menu every time you boot then you have to add
the commando @{b}nokey@{ub} in your @{"startup-sequence" link "Install" 0}. This is favourable for
floppy discs with more than one application or game.

If you call BangerMenu without any parameters you have to press the @{b}Caps Lock@{ub} key
or the @{b}Leftmousebotton@{ub} to start the menu. If you did not press the @{b}Caps Lock@{ub}
key or the @{b}Leftmousebotton@{ub} the ordinary @{b}startup-sequence@{ub} will be executed.

BangerMenu can be cancelled by pressing the @{b}close@{ub} gadget, @{b}escape@{ub} or the @{b}q@{ub} key. In
this case your ordinary startup-sequence will be continued.

New at version 2.0 you can load a monitordriver.
@{b}1.@{ub} Setpatch must run before BangerMenu.
@{b}2.@{ub} If VGAOnly in the DEVS:Monitors-Dir then must the program run before BangerMenu, too.
@{b}3.@{ub} You must give the monitordriver name and the idnumber.

Look at example:

@{b}BangerMenu MT=@{ub}@{fg highlight}DEVS:Monitors/VGA@{fg text} @{b}monitorid@{ub}=@{fg highlight}233508@{fg text}

Here is a list of IDs and there solutions

@{b}   MONITORID    MONITORDRIVER          SOLUTIONS@{ub}
    102400      DEVS:Monitors/NTSC      640*200    ;standard (USA)
    167936      DEVS:Monitors/PAL       640*256    ;standard (Europe)
    233508      DEVS:Monitors/Multiscan 640*480
    430116      DEVS:Monitors/Euro72    640*400
    561192      DEVS:Monitors/Super72   800*600
    626688      DEVS:Monitors/DblNTSC   640*400
    692224      DEVS:Monitors/DblPAL    640*512

This list is not complete. For more IDnumber you can look at the includes
@{b}graphics/modeid.@{ub}(@{b}i@{ub}/@{b}h@{ub}) or sent me @{"Mail" link "Autor" 0}
this the solution.
It is possible to represent the solution of a graphicboard like CyberVision on
BangerMenu. You must only know the monitorID-number. To get the number look
at the developersoftware.
New at version 2.01 you can use @{b}BangerMonitorID@{ub} to get the ID-number of any solution
you want.
@endnode
@node "Tastatur" "Keyboard control"
@next "config"
@prev "usage"
@{b}Keyboard control@{ub}


@{fg highlight}During startup@{fg text}
  @{b}CAPS-Lock-key@{ub}: @{b}BangerMenu@{ub} appear
@{b}Leftmousebotton@{ub}: @{b}BangerMenu@{ub} appear


@{fg highlight}BangerMenu Work@{fg text}
@{fg highlight}Cursor@{fg text}    @{b}Up@{ub}: active the gadget before
              if this gadget the last one, then active the gadget in the
              next columm
    +  @{fg highlight}Shift@{fg text}: the first gadget in this columm
        @{b}Down@{ub}: active the next gadget, if this gadget the last one,
              then active the first gadget in the next columm
    +  @{fg highlight}Shift@{fg text}: the last gadget in this columm
        @{b}Left@{ub}: the next columm will active is this the last columm
              on this page the next page will represent
    +  @{fg highlight}Shift@{fg text}: the first columm of the page will active
    +   @{fg highlight}Ctrl@{fg text}: the page before will active
       @{b}Right@{ub}: the gadget in the next columm will active, is this the
              last columm on this page the next page will active
    +  @{fg highlight}Shift@{fg text}: the last columm of the page will active
    +   @{fg highlight}Ctrl@{fg text}: the next page will active, if this the last
              page, the first one will represent

 @{b}>@{ub}          : a page to right
 @{b}<@{ub}          : a page to left

 @{b}Return@{ub}     : active gadget executing (equal mouseklick on gadget)

 @{b}q,Q,ESC@{ub}    : quit @{b}BangerMenu@{ub} withou doing nothing, the normal
              Startup-sequence will executed (equal to click on @{b}CLOSE@{ub}-
              Gadget of the window or @{b}QUIT@{ub} in the Screen Menu)
@endnode
@node "config" "How to setup a configuration"
@next "Fileconfig"
@prev "Tastatur"
@{b}How to setup a configuration@{ub}

New at version 3.3 you can give the config every name you want. If @{b}BangeMenu@{ub}
called without a configfile then @{b}BangeMenu@{ub} search in active dir or S:-dir
for @{b}BangeMenu.Prefs@{ub}.

example:
@{b}MENU@{ub}
 @{fg highlight}Entry1@{fg text} @{b}MKEY@{ub} @{fg highlight}1@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight}Entry2@{fg text} @{b}MKEY@{ub} @{fg highlight}2@{fg text}
 ñ
 ñ
@{b}ENDMENU@{ub}

The @{b}MENU@{ub} entry in the config make a Screen Menu.
The Screen Menu will be define between @{b}MENU@{ub} and @{b}ENDMENU@{ub}.
In this config @{fg highlight}Eintrag1 Eintrag2@{fg text}.
@{b}MKEY@{ub} is the shortcut for the Screen Menu entry.
Here is @{fg highlight}Eintrag1@{fg text} the key @{fg highlight}1@{fg text} and @{fg highlight}Eintrag2@{fg text} the key @{fg highlight}2@{fg text}.
The end of the Screen Menu must be define by @{b}ENDMENU@{ub}.
You can define max. 50 Screen Menu entry.

@{fg highlight}Entry1@{fg text}
@{b}COLTITLE@{ub} @{fg highlight}ColummTitle1@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight}programname1
 programpath1
 programname2
 programpath2@{fg text} @{b}[C]@{ub}
@{fg highlight} programname3
 programpath3
 ñ
 ñ@{fg text}
@{b}COLTITLE@{ub} @{fg highlight}ColummTitle2@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight}programname4
 programpath4
 programname5
 programpath5
 programname6
 programpath6@{fg text} @{b}[C]@{ub}
@{fg highlight} ñ
 ñ@{fg text}
@{b}END@{ub} @{fg highlight}Entry1@{fg text}
@{fg highlight}Entry2@{fg text}
 ñ
 ñ

Every Screen Menu entry must be define @{fg highlight}Entry1@{fg text} and @{b}END@{ub} @{fg highlight}Entry1@{fg text} !
The @{b}COLTITLE@{ub} give a columm the title. The follow names are the gadgetsname with
programpath. You can define 50 columms.
At every Screen Menu you can define till 2560 gadget on till 10 pages
The parameter @{b}[C]@{ub} can you use by games,demos or programs to change
the dir to programm.

DonÇt use at the end of the config the word @{b}ENDE@{ub} (the german word
for end). I have remove it since version 1.220. Thanks goto canadian.
For further information please have a look at the configuration file of
the program package.
For batchfiles without s-bit use EXECUTE <batchfile>.
@endnode
